Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.53,1:34:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:48.73,1:34:50.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He understands how to go on errands now.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.76,1:34:52.23,Studio,,0,0,0,,Will he be fine?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.90,1:34:52.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Also how to pay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.50,1:34:55.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the names of various products.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.44,1:34:58.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Alright and today it's collagen, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.24,1:35:01.51,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.51,1:35:06.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,During the training his father made him buy chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.81,1:35:06.41,Studio,,0,0,0,,Changed to chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.41,1:35:08.41,Studio,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.51,1:35:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though he was finally able to say collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.55,1:35:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Please repeat it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.85,1:35:14.05,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.05,1:35:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thighs?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.76,1:35:18.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is a pork specialty butcher.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.52,1:35:23.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She thought he confused it with pork thighs so that's what she gave him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.36,1:35:28.74,Studio,,0,0,0,,He's watching it all from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.77,1:35:30.07,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Mama, open up please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.74,1:35:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.07,1:35:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you purchase?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.27,1:35:33.17,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.17,1:35:36.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No no, it's meat from pig legs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.18,1:35:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao, are you having fun?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.31,1:35:38.91,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.91,1:35:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand you are having fun but
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.12,1:35:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.12,1:35:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to get it {\alphaFF\t(1051,1051,\alpha0)}for papa, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.59,1:35:47.95,Studio,,0,0,0,,- He's not listening.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.65,1:35:47.95,Studio,,0,0,0,,- He's not listening.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.15,1:35:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I am about to get mad. {\alphaFF\t(1560,1560,\alpha0)}Listen to what I am telling you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.09,1:35:53.56,Studio,,0,0,0,,There it is. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.46,1:35:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.63,1:35:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She's getting mad.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.63,1:35:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She can get really scary during those times.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.57,1:36:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When he does things half-hearted
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.67,1:36:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,she will get mad.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.17,1:36:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that about her.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.90,1:36:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want her to get mad more often but...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.11,1:36:10.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The mother isn't ordinary either.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.04,1:36:12.04,Studio,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.68,1:36:15.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's a top athlete who aimed for the olympics in badminton.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.28,1:36:17.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But she retired when they married
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.95,1:36:21.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and she continued fighting for victory as a mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.42,1:36:27.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to raising her son she's lenient with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.86,1:36:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's 3 but I still see him as a baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.90,1:36:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.30,1:36:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just like a miniature of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.74,1:36:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is cuter.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.31,1:36:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're losing out.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.78,1:36:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.55,1:36:47.75,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.85,1:36:50.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Another try for collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.58,1:36:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.09,1:36:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.05,1:36:57.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's walking weird this time.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.76,1:36:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.66,1:36:59.96,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.96,1:37:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.58,1:37:02.74,Studio,,0,0,0,,He's messing around.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.76,1:37:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.86,1:37:05.83,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.83,1:37:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.87,1:37:09.10,Studio,,0,0,0,,He's gonna get something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.20,1:37:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.17,1:37:13.32,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's unfair. She's saying it with him all the way to the shop door.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.97,1:37:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.00,1:37:13.44,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.44,1:37:15.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This time he can't forget, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.94,1:37:18.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since he's already at the shop.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.38,1:37:19.75,Studio,,0,0,0,,Right at the shop.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.01,1:37:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.38,1:37:21.28,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.95,1:37:27.99,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.99,1:37:29.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was finally able to say it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.59,1:37:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please repeat it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.12,1:37:34.96,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Collagen, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.89,1:37:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.09,1:37:36.00,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.00,1:37:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Collagen soup base?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.16,1:37:39.07,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.17,1:37:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing. How nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.33,1:37:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No no no.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.10,1:37:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like moms wish made its way there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.01,1:37:49.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Not only her wish but also her love has made it there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.14,1:37:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I will take 100 yen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.21,1:37:56.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He paid for it. His mother will be delighted.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.58,1:38:00.65,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I bought collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.68,1:38:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought it?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.75,1:38:01.02,Studio,,0,0,0,,Finally.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.65,1:38:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. {\alphaFF\t(1793,1793,\alpha0)}You really helped me out.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.52,1:38:06.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To buy a mere collagen bag
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.33,1:38:08.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it still took 34 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.96,1:38:14.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But his father is surprised by his sons development in these 34 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.43,1:38:20.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His development since he became 3 years old {\alphaFF\t(2894,2894,\alpha0)}has been remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.14,1:38:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like he is breaking out of his {\alphaFF\t(3392,3392,\alpha0)}shell.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.55,1:38:32.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Changing from a baby into a boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.65,1:38:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I want him to come out fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.92,1:38:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to accomplish anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.16,1:38:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And become a boy who isn't prone to crying.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.83,1:38:43.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,40 minutes have passed.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.66,1:38:46.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Time for a player substitution in the second-half.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.57,1:38:51.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Tanaka papa will switch with the mother and challenge Mao to a new errand.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.34,1:38:53.34,Studio,,0,0,0,,This time it's further away.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.47,1:38:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye bye Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.14,1:38:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao can you help out?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.21,1:38:55.27,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.27,1:38:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.48,1:39:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite food is?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.31,1:39:00.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The errand is to get food that his father likes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.05,1:39:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(526.5,58)}Chicken Nanban: fried chicken with vinegar and tartar sauce​
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.05,1:39:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicken Nanban.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.05,1:39:02.72,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken Nanban.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.72,1:39:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What type of meat is needed for it?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.58,1:39:07.99,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.99,1:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make a dance to help you remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.36,1:39:11.36,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chi-ck-en thi-gh-s.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.36,1:39:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey hey hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.13,1:39:15.96,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.56,1:39:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice. You dance well.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.06,1:39:18.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.20,1:39:20.20,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.20,1:39:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Chicken thighs. We don't have enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.70,1:39:24.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And one more ingredient.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.67,1:39:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What vegetable looks like my face?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.47,1:39:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is pea green.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.54,1:39:31.58,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.18,1:39:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Just like my...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.58,1:39:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the size of my face. Cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.71,1:39:37.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Cabbage which looks like his fathers face.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.08,1:39:40.32,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,We are lacking it today.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.58,1:39:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lacking in cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.32,1:39:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lacking in cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.52,1:39:45.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's clever to use his body to help him remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.52,1:39:47.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What do you think, mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.19,1:39:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's becoming hyper.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.40,1:39:51.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Is that not good?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.23,1:39:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs. Thump. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.57,1:39:57.50,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.50,1:40:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Cabbage too. Thump.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.47,1:40:05.41,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,But cabbages are big.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.24,1:40:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They are big but they have entered your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.41,1:40:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And the third item, mayonnaise, have entered too.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.68,1:40:09.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's also getting mayonnaise?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.72,1:40:11.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For the tartar sauce.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.92,1:40:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright Mao, {\alphaFF\t(920,920,\alpha0)}this is a good luck charm.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.39,1:40:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be more direct.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.99,1:40:21.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And now the mother is going to coach him.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.13,1:40:23.13,Studio,,0,0,0,,Is she mad?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.86,1:40:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait, it's mama.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.53,1:40:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.60,1:40:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.43,1:40:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's dangerous to let Mao out when he gets this hyper.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.30,1:40:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And because he's hyper...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.64,1:40:33.24,Studio,,0,0,0,,So strict.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.77,1:40:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please change your tone a bit
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.18,1:40:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell him he needs to do it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.05,1:40:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget to put his jacket on.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.95,1:40:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.42,1:40:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.45,1:40:48.15,Studio,,0,0,0,,Come on, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.55,1:40:51.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She knows it won't go well if he's in a playful mood.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.19,1:40:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.06,1:40:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please listen seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.23,1:40:59.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To turn him in a serious state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.93,1:41:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand to attention. Beep.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.53,1:41:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa{\alphaFF\t(893,893,\alpha0)} he always does his best in rugby, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.74,1:41:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And in order to do my training
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.94,1:41:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.87,1:41:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,eat mama's cooking today
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.61,1:41:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and do my best in tomorrows training.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.61,1:41:15.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has training camp starting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.61,1:41:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao, you are a boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.12,1:41:18.65,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:18.65,1:41:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.65,1:41:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect you to help us out properly.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.82,1:41:24.32,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.32,1:41:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.29,1:41:26.89,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.89,1:41:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa believes in you, Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.46,1:41:30.36,Studio,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172.125,73)}His mood changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.36,1:41:30.93,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.93,1:41:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the wristband {\alphaFF\t(1990,1990,\alpha0)}that I always wear during matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.80,1:41:39.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mao feels like a Japanese representative.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.31,1:41:41.74,Studio,,0,0,0,,{\pos(166.5,75)}He looks so happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.97,1:41:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa will always protect you.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.28,1:41:49.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's getting ingredients for chicken Nanban.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.62,1:41:56.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Chicken thighs, {\alphaFF\t(1418,1418,\alpha0)}cabbage{\alphaFF\t(3253,3253,\alpha0)} and mayonnaise for the tartar sauce is what he needs to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.16,1:41:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.09,1:41:59.53,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.53,1:42:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.29,1:42:01.73,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.73,1:42:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.96,1:42:04.63,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Off I go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.63,1:42:06.20,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Bye bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.20,1:42:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.20,1:42:07.43,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.10,1:42:13.67,Studio,,0,0,0,,He started sprinting.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.18,1:42:20.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His mother is peeking out from the blinds.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.78,1:42:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not long within sight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.78,1:42:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's not long within sight.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.15,1:42:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He started running the moment before I lost sight of him.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.52,1:42:28.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What is their state of mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.02,1:42:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel anxious when I can't see him. At least over there I could still see him.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.36,1:42:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't feel anxious.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.29,1:42:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm about to cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.33,1:42:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You are really on the verge.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.93,1:42:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I can feel his amazing growth.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.80,1:42:45.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just previously it was the collagen thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.97,1:42:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it amazing?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.81,1:42:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.04,1:42:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That he didn't complain {\alphaFF\t(1356,1356,\alpha0)}and said that he can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.82,1:43:03.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His big sister is the one who taught him how to shop only 11 days ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.46,1:43:04.79,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,There's no natto.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.09,1:43:10.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mao, who didn't want to go,{\alphaFF\t(1758,1758,\alpha0)} and as soon as his sister let go of him...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.50,1:43:12.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was his state.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.53,1:43:13.43,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.10,1:43:15.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And they wondered if he could be relied on.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.37,1:43:19.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But in no time he has changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.87,1:43:23.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has always done the railway crossing training with great joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.35,1:43:29.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since he loves trains.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.18,1:43:33.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately he's not seeing trains today.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.65,1:43:40.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's passing behind him but he's not noticing cause he's on an errand.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.44,1:44:00.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Moments before in front of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.08,1:44:04.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is now a boy who just bought collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.05,1:44:05.52,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.62,1:44:08.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has arrived at the large supermarket.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.49,1:44:10.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Poultry, cabbage and mayonnaise.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.92,1:44:13.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Take the children sized basket.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.23,1:44:14.96,Studio,,0,0,0,,Will he remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.66,1:44:19.37,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Where are the vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.43,1:44:20.20,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.37,1:44:21.33,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.07,1:44:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.33,1:44:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I will take you there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.33,1:44:24.44,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The vegetable that is pea green.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.44,1:44:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The pea green one?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.37,1:44:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The pea green what?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.57,1:44:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.64,1:44:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here and over there you can find pea green ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.91,1:44:33.08,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Is this pea green?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.08,1:44:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is lettuce.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.75,1:44:37.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Isn't this much smaller than his fathers head?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.62,1:44:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And what else do you need to get?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.19,1:44:42.76,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Meat from chicken thighs.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.76,1:44:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Meat from chicken thighs?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.86,1:44:48.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has memorized "chicken thighs".
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.66,1:44:51.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the most important ingredient in chicken Nanban.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.06,1:44:56.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What will you make today?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.10,1:44:56.64,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Meat from chicken thighs and...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.64,1:44:58.67,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Pea green vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.67,1:44:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Pea green?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.27,1:45:05.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The fact that he could say chicken thighs but didn't say lettuce made the store assistant concerned.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.38,1:45:07.58,Studio,,0,0,0,,What an amazing shop assistant.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.71,1:45:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it lettuce or cabbage?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.01,1:45:09.48,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.11,1:45:12.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Small children always confuse lettuce and cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.79,1:45:14.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Is he getting both?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.45,1:45:15.72,Studio,,0,0,0,,Gonna be heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.72,1:45:17.29,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Huh, what about daikon?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.29,1:45:19.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was not asked to get daikon.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.79,1:45:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You are also getting daikon?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.56,1:45:22.70,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.33,1:45:24.80,Studio,,0,0,0,,Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.70,1:45:24.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's also getting daikon?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.30,1:45:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't carry this huge thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.53,1:45:27.43,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I can.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.53,1:45:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't carry it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.20,1:45:33.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The shop assistant is worried that he was not asked to get all these things for the errand.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.71,1:45:36.01,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Mao will carry this.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.01,1:45:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You will carry it?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.21,1:45:41.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's carrying it like a rugby ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.31,1:45:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Cabbage or lettuce. {\alphaFF\t(2528,2528,\alpha0)}Which one is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.95,1:45:45.28,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,1007)}Lettuce.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.28,1:45:47.28,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\pos(533.25,1007)}This is...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.65,1:45:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.49,1:45:51.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Which one is his fathers head.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.76,1:45:54.39,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The one like my father...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.73,1:45:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it this one?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.39,1:45:55.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He choose the cabbage.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.70,1:45:59.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He completely forgot the mayonnaise.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.97,1:46:04.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He prefers it to be heavy. That way he's guaranteed praises from his father.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.87,1:46:07.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But will he be okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.91,1:46:09.07,Studio,,0,0,0,,Heavy. Heavy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.27,1:46:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So tough.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.28,1:46:17.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The assistant to the shop manager ran over to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.15,1:46:21.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The cabbage fits perfectly in the ladybug. {\alphaFF\t(2223,2223,\alpha0)}I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.19,1:46:24.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His father thought of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:24.92,1:46:26.36,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Bye bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.96,1:46:34.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The chicken meat is also in his bag.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.60,1:46:37.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In his hands is the daikon he wasn't asked to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.52,1:46:56.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And this is how it usually ends with the daikon.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.52,1:47:00.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is what happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.56,1:47:01.19,Studio,,0,0,0,,He's dragging it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:01.79,1:47:03.19,Studio,,0,0,0,,Oh no no.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.40,1:47:06.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A gravel road.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.70,1:47:09.03,Studio,,0,0,0,,No good.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.97,1:47:11.60,Studio,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:10.50,1:47:12.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He lifted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.34,1:47:14.84,Studio,,0,0,0,,It's popping out.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.37,1:47:15.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Saved it from severe damage.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.61,1:47:17.48,Studio,,0,0,0,,It's popping out.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.52,1:47:25.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A train.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.35,1:47:29.05,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Waah, {\alphaFF\t(591,591,\alpha0)}hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.05,1:47:30.56,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The train is coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.56,1:47:32.19,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Hurry. The train is co...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.19,1:47:35.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He can still run with the daikon.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.40,1:47:41.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No reason for the staff to be worried. He's watching from a distance and with composure.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.53,1:47:44.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He really loves trains.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.37,1:47:46.07,Studio,,0,0,0,,He's waving at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:49.17,1:47:52.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After this crossing he's almost home.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.25,1:47:59.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Another train.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.95,1:47:59.82,Studio,,0,0,0,,Another.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.95,1:48:03.76,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.76,1:48:06.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's going back to the tracks?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.29,1:48:09.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That poor daikon is on a journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.74,1:48:25.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,We underestimated him.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.41,1:48:29.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With a height of 94 cm and a weight of 13 kg.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.15,1:48:33.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Without fail
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.95,1:48:38.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,this small giant is walking with all his might.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.70,1:48:49.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Mao who has returned has the face of a boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.80,1:48:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.77,1:48:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.65,1:49:04.35,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.05,1:49:06.35,Studio,,0,0,0,,He did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.35,1:49:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.02,1:49:11.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A try (rugby move) into his fathers arms.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.32,1:49:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You did your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.06,1:49:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You properly...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.39,1:49:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. You bought it?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.49,1:49:16.76,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Here is...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.76,1:49:19.40,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,A hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.40,1:49:22.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The plastic bag also did its best.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.03,1:49:24.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was able to bring the daikon all the way home.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.74,1:49:26.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.87,1:49:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you buy daikon?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.54,1:49:33.35,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.18,1:49:36.72,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Bought it since they had daikon available.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.72,1:49:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it was available?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.12,1:49:38.68,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:39.52,1:49:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.45,1:49:42.39,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.29,1:49:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's also eat daikon.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.69,1:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus. Focus.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.42,1:49:48.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The father said: "Let's make grated daikon."
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.80,1:49:51.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the chicken Nanban
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.33,1:49:56.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,is a nostalgic Japanese taste his wife made when his team went to New Zealand.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.00,1:50:01.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since he didn't purchase mayonaise they made ponzu mixed with grated daikon.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.67,1:50:02.31,Studio,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.08,1:50:05.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They made soup pasta with the collagen.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:05.41,1:50:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.61,1:50:10.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Todays chicken Nanban is exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.65,1:50:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.68,1:50:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.69,1:50:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really delicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:14.75,1:50:17.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The collagen was hard to get.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.32,1:50:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The pasta is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.79,1:50:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna try the daikon {\alphaFF\t(1857,1857,\alpha0)}you bought, Mao?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.06,1:50:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you bought Mao.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.23,1:50:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2627,0,\alphaFF)}It's an acquired taste after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:34.24,1:50:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That was funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.94,1:50:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.01,1:50:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a short movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.24,1:50:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.65,1:50:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That was quite something. He went so many times.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.68,1:50:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.38,1:50:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,His expression changed moment by moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.45,1:50:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The pride felt {\alphaFF\t(1893,1893,\alpha0)}from having a duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:53.79,1:50:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How he went to the butcher in front of his house
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.46,1:50:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and to think they went with the supermarket right after.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.70,1:50:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's indeed unusual.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.73,1:51:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The way his father made him remember in a fun way with his body.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.67,1:51:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was spectacular. We are like two peas in a pod.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.87,1:51:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I also do that to easily remember things.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.88,1:51:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When I try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.54,1:51:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But while it works for me {\alphaFF\t(2727,2727,\alpha0)}the mother said: "No good".
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.35,1:51:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he was like: "I'm sorry."
Dialogue: 0,1:51:17.12,1:51:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that his expression changed  instantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.25,1:51:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a switch being flipped.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.25,1:51:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And for our next errand...
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.19,1:51:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,An errand with a strict code and a warm embrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.23,1:51:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(807.001,155.807)}Fukushima ● Aizuwakamatsu
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.53,1:51:33.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The thing that everyone knows in Aizuwakamatsu city.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.93,1:51:36.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Here the kids in primary school
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.90,1:51:41.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,have to follow a strict code.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.54,1:51:44.11,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,The Aizukko Code
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.11,1:51:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(531,54.39)}Specific to the town of Aizuwakamatsu.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.11,1:51:46.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is the Aizukko Code.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.88,1:51:48.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.18,1:51:49.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Empathize with people.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.85,1:51:52.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Say thank you and sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.22,1:51:54.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Persevere and more.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.55,1:51:57.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even when adults look at it, their backs straighten up.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:58.09,1:52:01.89,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,Do what you must. {\alphaFF\t(1990,1990,\alpha0)}Don't do what you must not.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.89,1:52:05.66,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,The things you should not do, you must not do.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.83,1:52:06.83,Studio,,0,0,0,,How wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.43,1:52:12.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since the time of Byakkotai samurai the rules have been continuously passed down for the children.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.10,1:52:17.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When you ask both adults and children in this area {\alphaFF\t(3295,3295,\alpha0)}their backs straighten up.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.51,1:52:23.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It is not just history, {\alphaFF\t(2390,2390,\alpha0)}it is the honored code.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.58,1:52:29.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And when he breaks the code this boy immediately bursts into tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.86,1:52:33.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The youngest child, Yuuto, and his two sisters.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.89,1:52:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(401.625,791)\fs30}{\alphaFF\t(0,521,\alpha0)}Second daughter
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.89,1:52:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(249.75,293)\fs30}{\alphaFF\t(0,521,\alpha0)}Oldest daughter
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.89,1:52:41.00,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\pos(704.25,815)}{\alphaFF\t(0,521,\alpha0)}Yuuto
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.00,1:52:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\pos(455.875,712.325)}{\alphaFF\t(0,350,\alpha0)}Second daughter
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.00,1:52:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(240.75,317)\fs30}{\alphaFF\t(0,350,\alpha0)}Oldest daughter
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.00,1:52:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(604.125,375)\fs40}{\alphaFF\t(0,350,\alpha0)}Mother
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.00,1:52:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(766.125,245)\fs40}{\alphaFF\t(0,350,\alpha0)}Father
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.13,1:52:37.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Before his bedtime his parents used to read him the declaration.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.30,1:52:41.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And as he grew up he came to remember it by heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.27,1:52:45.97,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Having pride in Aizu town {\alphaFF\t(1886,1886,\alpha0)}and listening to the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.97,1:52:49.47,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Do what you must. {\alphaFF\t(1824,1824,\alpha0)}Don't do what you must not.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.47,1:52:52.71,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The things you should not do, you must not do.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.71,1:52:54.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though he still can't read.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.35,1:52:58.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The samurai Yuuto. {\alphaFF\t(1153,1153,\alpha0)}He's been getting energetic since moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.95,1:53:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuto please answer it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.52,1:53:02.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Hey hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.46,1:53:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember to say "hello".
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.79,1:53:05.96,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Hello hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.96,1:53:07.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's his sister in primary school.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.69,1:53:10.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She is reading the script her mother gave her.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.66,1:53:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(3256,0,\alphaFF)\pos(880.875,893)}Memo
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.56,1:53:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot something at home{\alphaFF\t(3227,3227,\alpha0)} so can you get mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.43,1:53:17.80,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,She said that she forgot something.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.80,1:53:21.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She usually does forget but today it's just an act.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.91,1:53:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot my sheet music so please bring it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.24,1:53:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.88,1:53:28.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like in the script.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.01,1:53:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuto, this is bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.11,1:53:30.02,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Um?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.02,1:53:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Momo said she forgot her sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.55,1:53:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it there? {\alphaFF\t(1423,1423,\alpha0)}Can you take a look?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.62,1:53:39.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She uses them to practice the piano with her mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.66,1:53:45.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Found it. It's the sheet music that she uses to practice for the choir class.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.96,1:53:45.83,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.46,1:53:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.53,1:53:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's noon we better hurry or it will be too late.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.40,1:53:54.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The 4th period ends at 12:05. {\alphaFF\t(3459,3459,\alpha0)}There's more than 1 hour left.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.81,1:53:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to take it there, Yuuto.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:56.81,1:53:59.88,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Will Yuuto go all by himself?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.88,1:54:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you should "do what you must"{\alphaFF\t(1521,1521,\alpha0)}, please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:02.31,1:54:04.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The code says: "Do what you must."
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.68,1:54:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Please {\alphaFF\t(1425,1425,\alpha0)}go, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.15,1:54:06.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\pos(540,1005)}He won't cry.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.22,1:54:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.42,1:54:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.09,1:54:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't go inside the school wearing a raincoat and drenched.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:12.46,1:54:15.96,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,When I enter {\alphaFF\t(1120,1120,\alpha0)}and take off my raincoat {\alphaFF\t(2488,2488,\alpha0)}I should wipe myself with a towel.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.96,1:54:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.83,1:54:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.83,1:54:19.70,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Must do what I must.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.70,1:54:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it "Do what I must"?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.13,1:54:24.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Things you must do{\alphaFF\t(1392,1392,\alpha0)} and things you must not. {\alphaFF\t(2893,2893,\alpha0)}It's difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.17,1:54:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you should do what you must. {\alphaFF\t(1556,1556,\alpha0)}Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.04,1:54:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.28,1:54:33.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister also goes to her primary school by foot
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.85,1:54:41.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but worried about Yuuto his mother found a route that has fewer cars passing by.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.29,1:54:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuto, you are capable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.52,1:54:45.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She also believes in Aizukko.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.09,1:54:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you fine going this way?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.76,1:54:50.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They have set up the premise for Yuuto's errand.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.20,1:54:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.26,1:54:53.70,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Off I go.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.17,1:54:58.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The youngest of a 4 generation 10 people big family.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.70,1:55:01.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Until now, everyone has done everything for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.34,1:55:05.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sometimes shy, prone to crying and frights.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.08,1:55:07.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.01,1:55:12.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He knows that today he must "do what he must".
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.95,1:55:15.12,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I better hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.12,1:55:17.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He should hand it to her during lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.16,1:55:22.03,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I better go.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.36,1:55:24.30,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I better go.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.30,1:55:26.83,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,To Momoka. {\alphaFF\t(1285,1285,\alpha0)}For Momoka.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.83,1:55:30.60,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Because she forgot {\alphaFF\t(1324,1324,\alpha0)}the sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.27,1:55:31.33,Studio,,0,0,0,,Remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.60,1:55:32.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Don't do what you must not.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.64,1:55:35.41,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Is our school really
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.41,1:55:36.98,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,all this way?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.98,1:55:42.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's right. It's 2 km one-way. 4 both ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.01,1:55:43.35,Studio,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.25,1:55:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That much?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.12,1:55:46.12,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.12,1:55:49.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's been told that he has to cross like this when he enters primary school.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.65,1:55:52.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His mother has been training him.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.72,1:55:56.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Momo is in her first year and has 2 years to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.46,1:55:58.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The shy Yuuto.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.73,1:56:01.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Can he approach the reception?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.90,1:56:04.50,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.50,1:56:06.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was able to.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:05.20,1:56:06.64,Studio,,0,0,0,,Excellent.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.11,1:56:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Momo's...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.27,1:56:09.07,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.07,1:56:10.88,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Mo...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.57,1:56:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.88,1:56:12.81,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The third year student Momo
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.81,1:56:15.35,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I brought her the thing she forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:15.35,1:56:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now {\alphaFF\t(1386,1386,\alpha0)}she's in a class
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.55,1:56:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but I will open it for you. {\alphaFF\t(922,922,\alpha0)}Please wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.92,1:56:24.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He arrived 30 minutes before time.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.76,1:56:25.76,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:24.12,1:56:26.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister is still in class.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.59,1:56:28.03,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Since I am wet
Dialogue: 0,1:56:28.03,1:56:30.43,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,the towel is in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.39,1:56:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in your bag?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.43,1:56:33.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like his mother told him. {\alphaFF\t(1888,1888,\alpha0)}Wipe yourself when you enter.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:33.87,1:56:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Great that you are on an errand.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:35.43,1:56:36.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's a kid with common sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.47,1:56:40.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's right. {\alphaFF\t(787,787,\alpha0)}Put the slippers on too.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.01,1:56:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the principal's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.24,1:56:44.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The principal's office?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.81,1:56:48.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Some might be terrified of such a prospect but
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.41,1:56:50.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yuuto has no idea what kind of room that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.72,1:56:54.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's fine. He is being welcomed inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:54.45,1:56:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(1792,0,\alphaFF)}Sorry for intruding.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.32,1:56:58.89,Studio,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172.125,77)}Makes you anxious.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:59.36,1:57:01.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the principal.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.19,1:57:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.53,1:57:03.66,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:03.93,1:57:06.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This school has faced these tiny visitors
Dialogue: 0,1:57:06.56,1:57:10.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and boasts of doing so for over 140 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.34,1:57:13.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the two successive female principal's.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.27,1:57:14.34,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.34,1:57:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:16.74,1:57:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I look inside?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.44,1:57:21.38,Studio,,0,0,0,,Tightly.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.55,1:57:22.08,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,It has been taped up.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:22.08,1:57:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that it doesn't get wet.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.82,1:57:28.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to avoid getting the important sheet music wet.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.39,1:57:31.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She wrapped it in 40 plastic bags.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.09,1:57:33.32,Studio,,0,0,0,,That many!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.09,1:57:35.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It finally came out.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.76,1:57:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.96,1:57:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheet music for the choir class.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.44,1:57:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.84,1:57:48.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has waited 20 minutes at the roomy principal's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.14,1:57:49.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Respecting the elders.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.94,1:57:52.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Persevering. Just like the Aizukko pledge.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.84,1:57:54.84,Studio,,0,0,0,,How admirable.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:58.92,1:58:00.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's his sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.09,1:58:02.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She was called to the principal's office.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.95,1:58:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:05.46,1:58:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuto.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.62,1:58:08.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He arrived 30 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.89,1:58:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.53,1:58:14.07,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,I came here by myself right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:14.07,1:58:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(1752,0,\alphaFF)}How remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.47,1:58:17.87,Studio,,0,0,0,,A kind sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.67,1:58:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You did your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:17.94,1:58:19.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What a moving response.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:19.60,1:58:22.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:22.57,1:58:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Wait. {\alphaFF\t(1727,1727,\alpha0)}Where's the script?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.48,1:58:27.78,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,The script?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:26.31,1:58:27.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Something is missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.85,1:58:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2820,0,\alphaFF)}There should be a script here. Not just this.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.95,1:58:34.49,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Mama probably forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.39,1:58:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama, you shouldn't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.56,1:58:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's a musical there is the sheet music but also a separate script.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:42.43,1:58:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.53,1:58:45.80,Studio,,0,0,0,,Oh no.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.26,1:58:48.83,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Mama probably forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:50.74,1:58:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama, you shouldn't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.24,1:58:57.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since it's a musical there is the sheet music but also a separate script.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:57.14,1:58:59.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her mother didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:59.88,1:59:02.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's at home above the piano.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:59.04,1:59:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(558,427)}Script
Dialogue: 0,1:59:02.88,1:59:05.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The script. {\alphaFF\t(1257,1257,\alpha0)}What will they do?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:08.12,1:59:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. I will borrow it from someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:11.29,1:59:12.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,How good.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.82,1:59:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You still did your best.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.99,1:59:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.16,1:59:16.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A kind big sister.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.43,1:59:18.26,Studio,,0,0,0,,She's so kind.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.66,1:59:19.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister understands.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.70,1:59:22.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The hardship of a 2 km route, 4 km round-way trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.97,1:59:25.20,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Despite me coming by myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:25.20,1:59:27.77,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2060,0,\alphaFF)}And then it ended up like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.40,1:59:30.07,Studio,,0,0,0,,- Like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:27.01,1:59:30.07,Studio,,0,0,0,,- He's so serious. \N- He still brought it.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:28.97,1:59:33.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's fine. Your sister was truly happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:34.48,1:59:37.12,Studio,,0,0,0,,This is gut-wrenching.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:35.75,1:59:38.02,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,It was a failure.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:38.02,1:59:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't feel accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.85,1:59:41.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But you were told you didn't fail.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.32,1:59:46.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He opens the door with a gloomy feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.53,1:59:50.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2319,0,\alphaF)}Yuuto, welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:51.10,1:59:54.63,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,There was another thing she forgot.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.20,1:59:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.80,1:59:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you give her the sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:56.43,1:59:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:56.77,1:59:58.87,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.87,2:00:01.54,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,There was another thing she forgot.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.54,2:00:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.58,2:00:07.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What else did she forget besides the sheet music?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.71,2:00:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it. Found it.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.42,2:00:11.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The script.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.52,2:00:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry Yuuto.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:13.95,2:00:18.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She messed up with the preparation prior to today.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:14.95,2:00:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:19.02,2:00:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same cover. {\alphaFF\t(1726,1726,\alpha0)}What will we do?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:21.73,2:00:24.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though his sister told him it's fine she'll borrow it from someone.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:24.33,2:00:27.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He won't tell his mother that.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:29.43,2:00:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(4296,0,\alphaFF)}Yuuto. I'm sorry. {\alphaFF\t(2127,2127,\alpha0)\t(4296,0,\alphaFF)}I'm sorry. It's my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.24,2:00:37.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though he did it properly he still feels gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.68,2:00:40.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yuuto is not entering the house.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.35,2:00:45.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His mother has noticed Yuuto's wavering resolve.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:46.18,2:00:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go again?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.79,2:00:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you go?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:50.76,2:00:52.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He will go.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:51.96,2:00:54.63,Studio,,0,0,0,,It's 2 km.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.06,2:00:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's you, Yuuto, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:54.63,2:00:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.09,2:00:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:59.40,2:01:01.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Must do what you must.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:03.03,2:01:06.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He finally understands the meaning of it.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.24,2:01:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's you, Yuuto, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.07,2:01:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to cry, right? You can cry.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.78,2:01:15.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His mother embraces him and lets him cry it out.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.78,2:01:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.12,2:01:20.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,While crying he's still resolute and willing to go.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.75,2:01:25.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And when leaving the house...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:25.09,2:01:27.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He perfectly stops crying.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:34.87,2:01:37.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He departs with bravado.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:39.37,2:01:42.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The mother {\alphaFF\t(1189,1189,\alpha0)}feels a sense of heavy duty.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:46.34,2:01:49.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She can't stand in the way of Yuuto's sense of accomplishment.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:49.35,2:01:51.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Must do what she must do.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:55.22,2:01:59.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The noon class starts at 1:30. That's less than 30 minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:01.56,2:02:03.06,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(1155,0,\alphaFF)}I better go.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:03.39,2:02:06.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first time it took 40 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:06.63,2:02:09.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He won't make it if he isn't 10 minutes faster.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:09.97,2:02:12.84,Studio,,0,0,0,,- Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:10.50,2:02:12.84,Studio,,0,0,0,,- How does he have so much sense of responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:12.90,2:02:18.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite her feelings, his mother wants him to feel accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:18.28,2:02:20.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She must be stoic.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:23.31,2:02:25.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,15 minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.62,2:02:26.12,Studio,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.32,2:02:29.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's running rather than walking. \N He's running rather than walking.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.22,2:02:32.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the rain. He's made it half-way there.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:32.46,2:02:36.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is like the face of an athlete.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.53,2:02:39.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was rough and worrying.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:46.30,2:02:48.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Only 4 minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:48.94,2:02:51.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The rain has ceased.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.24,2:02:53.24,Studio,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.38,2:02:54.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's almost within sight of the school.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:58.52,2:03:02.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She got a call by her mother that Yuuto is coming back.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:03.45,2:03:05.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's coming back twice just for me?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:05.56,2:03:07.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister is in disbelief.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:09.19,2:03:11.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The school is right there.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:12.50,2:03:13.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What about the time?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:14.60,2:03:17.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Two minutes left. He can make it.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:20.10,2:03:22.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The crossing flags.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:22.74,2:03:25.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even at such a time he doesn't just run.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:25.08,2:03:27.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Do what you must.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:28.01,2:03:32.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But...{\alphaFF\t(2793,2793,\alpha0)}hurry. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,2:03:33.55,2:03:36.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The bell will sound in one minute.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:37.59,2:03:40.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister is so full of anxious excitement.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:46.06,2:03:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuuto, you totally did your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.67,2:03:50.40,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(1419,0,\alphaFF)}I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:52.87,2:03:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2424,0,\alphaFF)}But I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.74,2:03:58.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the bell.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:58.68,2:04:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:00.58,2:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm so happy. {\alphaFF\t(1054,1054,\alpha0)}Be happy.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:03.01,2:04:04.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shaving 10 minutes off his last time.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.85,2:04:06.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's at his limits.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:06.28,2:04:08.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He can't even celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:13.49,2:04:17.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His sister went back to the class right away.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:25.40,2:04:28.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mother, he managed to deliver the script.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:29.84,2:04:32.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's worried if it was alright to let him go twice.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:32.64,2:04:35.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's anxious until she sees Yuuto's face.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:35.88,2:04:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:37.18,2:04:39.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This face shows accomplishments.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:40.82,2:04:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:42.95,2:04:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You did your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:44.89,2:04:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Did you manage to go all the way?
Dialogue: 0,2:04:48.43,2:04:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was cold, right? I see. You did well.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:52.30,2:04:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. {\alphaFF\t(1186,1186,\alpha0)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:54.93,2:04:57.07,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Do what you must.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:57.07,2:04:59.04,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,Don't do what you must not.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:55.00,2:04:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:59.27,2:05:02.27,WhiteBlueBorder,,0,0,0,,You should not do what you must not.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.27,2:05:03.81,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:02.87,2:05:06.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,You can't see on his face that he ran 8 km.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:05.51,2:05:07.95,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:09.58,2:05:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Really amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:11.55,2:05:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What an errand, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:13.58,2:05:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:15.35,2:05:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ebizou, {\alphaFF\t(1092,1092,\alpha0)}you cried a bit, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:18.32,2:05:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I totally didn't.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:19.76,2:05:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing as expected.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:23.09,2:05:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother didn't intend it to happen but
Dialogue: 0,2:05:25.96,2:05:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they forgot it at home
Dialogue: 0,2:05:27.43,2:05:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was an errand to erase regret
Dialogue: 0,2:05:30.37,2:05:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and those tears she shed.\N {\alphaFF\t(2955,2955,\alpha0)}I don't know how to express it.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:34.84,2:05:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's to be praised after the first run alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:36.54,2:05:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's how it should be.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.98,2:05:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it was real the mother would go, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:42.21,2:05:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But if she went then the boy's sense of accomplishment would be diminished.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:47.39,2:05:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that his mother didn't go is truly love.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:50.29,2:05:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:51.22,2:05:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing how
Dialogue: 0,2:05:52.72,2:05:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it showed the soul of {\alphaFF\t(2093,2093,\alpha0)}Aizu. (In Fukushima prefecture)
Dialogue: 0,2:05:58.16,2:06:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Amami you kept saying that Aizu was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.53,2:06:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To see his face become determined
Dialogue: 0,2:06:06.94,2:06:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he carried the guilt that he had to go again but said he would "absolutely go".
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.98,2:06:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. So many things to it. His mother was the one who forgot yet...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:17.05,2:06:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah so many things in the mix.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:18.82,2:06:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was a little {\alphaFF\t(1319,1319,\alpha0)}heart-wrenching.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:21.82,2:06:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As we speak about it you are about to...
Dialogue: 0,2:06:23.05,2:06:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:23.85,2:06:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.56,2:06:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pull it back.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:26.79,2:06:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Both his mothers'
Dialogue: 0,2:06:28.66,2:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but also his sisters' bond was splendid.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:31.46,2:06:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When she says "I'm happy" and "Be happy" that really made me think
Dialogue: 0,2:06:36.37,2:06:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that their bond
Dialogue: 0,2:06:38.34,2:06:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has grown even stronger.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.31,2:06:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the next errand is the adventures of a girl.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.61,2:06:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Where both the father and the daughter are stubborn and they wont compromise.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.08,2:06:55.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There's a father who never gets angry {\alphaFF\t(3125,3125,\alpha0)}but he's so stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:57.12,2:07:01.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There's a father who never gets angry {\alphaFF\t(2892,2892,\alpha0)}but he's so stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:01.86,2:07:06.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His daughters always do what their father tells them to do.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:07.37,2:07:09.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The father is a 3rd generation member of the farm.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:09.83,2:07:13.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They produce dried kaki for luxurious gifting.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.41,2:07:16.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When talking about Matsusato's dried kaki
Dialogue: 0,2:07:16.67,2:07:20.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it's the high grade product that represents Yamanashi and shipped all over the country.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:20.01,2:07:22.48,Studio,,0,0,0,,Looks delicious.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:22.56,2:07:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\pos(866.25,211)}Yamanashi ● Koushuu
Dialogue: 0,2:07:21.88,2:07:24.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the distant mountains of Koushuu
Dialogue: 0,2:07:24.42,2:07:29.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Blessed with sun and well-drained soil they grow delicious kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:29.39,2:07:33.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the koufu basin a strong dry notherly wind blows.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:33.39,2:07:36.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the optimal climate for making dried kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:36.93,2:07:39.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It goes back in history.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.03,2:07:43.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In old woodblock prints the method of making dried kaki is depicted as well.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:42.70,2:07:44.70,Studio,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:45.14,2:07:50.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The time around late November is the most spectacular season of the year.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:49.21,2:07:51.21,Studio,,0,0,0,,How picturesque.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:50.71,2:07:53.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The drying kaki color the whole town.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:53.41,2:07:57.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It invites a loving motif for photographers in the prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:59.15,2:08:02.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The little sister Ririka will go on her first errand.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:58.72,2:08:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(142.875,367)}{\alphaFF\t(0,484,\alpha0)}Big sister
Dialogue: 0,2:07:58.72,2:08:04.52,PurpleFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(839.25,345)}{\alphaFF\t(0,484,\alpha0)}Ririka
Dialogue: 0,2:08:02.85,2:08:05.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She always copies her big sister.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:05.36,2:08:08.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Every year, at her big sisters elementary school, during this time
Dialogue: 0,2:08:08.63,2:08:10.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,they peel the kaki
Dialogue: 0,2:08:10.53,2:08:13.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and learn how to prepare them.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:13.20,2:08:15.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even households that don't make their own
Dialogue: 0,2:08:15.53,2:08:18.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the children all get to learn how to help out.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:18.64,2:08:21.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's how the children are raised here.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:21.81,2:08:25.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Through ages the families have gathered at home like this
Dialogue: 0,2:08:25.28,2:08:29.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And they peel the kaki all day for an entire week.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:25.94,2:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(703.125,219)}Son of \Ngreat-granduncle
Dialogue: 0,2:08:26.14,2:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(378,243)\fs40}Granduncle
Dialogue: 0,2:08:28.05,2:08:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(117,323)}Daughter of \Ngreat-granduncle
Dialogue: 0,2:08:28.21,2:08:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\pos(787.5,255)}Granduncle
Dialogue: 0,2:08:30.15,2:08:32.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If my sister helps out so will I!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:32.38,2:08:35.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Is she preventing her father from working?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:35.29,2:08:37.86,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:35.89,2:08:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How many is this?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:37.86,2:08:39.16,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:39.56,2:08:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifth one.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:40.66,2:08:44.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No no, she's seriously helping out.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:44.13,2:08:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to change our gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:46.40,2:08:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right or they will tear again. So please do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:50.67,2:08:52.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like a tissue box
Dialogue: 0,2:08:52.53,2:08:55.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,there are 100 single-use gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:55.24,2:08:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I will take this one.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:57.58,2:08:59.41,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,No more left.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:58.44,2:08:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Any left for me?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:59.41,2:09:00.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's already empty.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:00.68,2:09:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's none for your Papa, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:03.55,2:09:05.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This must be the errand.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:06.28,2:09:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go buy some?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:06.95,2:09:08.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The size is L(arge).
Dialogue: 0,2:09:08.72,2:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand L? What's it look like?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:11.79,2:09:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Single-use gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:14.93,2:09:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this good-luck charm.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:15.49,2:09:19.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There a microphone in the charm her mother made.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:19.23,2:09:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do. Yes you can. So do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:21.43,2:09:22.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her mothers' wish.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:22.67,2:09:24.84,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,You can do. Yes you can. So do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:24.07,2:09:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can go?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:25.57,2:09:28.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her mother who is a pâtissier is at work today.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:28.01,2:09:30.21,Studio,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:29.27,2:09:33.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the hardware store she needs L-sized gloves and string to hang the kaki with.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:33.54,2:09:36.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the drug store she needs to get snacks for 3 O'clock tea
Dialogue: 0,2:09:36.01,2:09:39.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and bandages for her father to wrap around his fingers.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:40.18,2:09:41.92,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I can do my best.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.92,2:09:43.02,Studio,,0,0,0,,She's quickly off.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:43.02,2:09:46.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's off in a light and good mood.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:50.26,2:09:53.20,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I can do it. I can do it. \N Yes, I can. Yes, I can.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:53.20,2:09:55.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As long as it's for her father.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:55.03,2:09:55.97,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I can do my best.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:55.97,2:09:59.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Mom, she can definitely do it and do her best at it.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.67,2:10:02.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ririka loves her dad so much.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:02.27,2:10:06.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her father who is responsible for the farm after her grandfather suddenly fell ill.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:06.68,2:10:09.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Actually there's a different part to him.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:11.82,2:10:14.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He can be seen on the stage
Dialogue: 0,2:10:15.52,2:10:19.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with various famous artists all over the country.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:19.69,2:10:22.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's a pro guitarist.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:23.86,2:10:26.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He made a band in junior high school.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:26.56,2:10:30.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He went to university in Tokyo and became a pro musician.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:30.70,2:10:33.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,You can do. Yes you can. So do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:33.44,2:10:38.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His fate has conflicted between what he wants to do and what he must do.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:43.41,2:10:48.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ririka is always following her sister around and loves being babied.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:48.55,2:10:51.89,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2960,0,\alphaFF)}I can do. Yes I can.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:54.93,2:10:56.23,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This song
Dialogue: 0,2:10:56.23,2:10:59.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ririka's father made a song with her in mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:59.10,2:11:02.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Title is: {\alphaFF\t(1219,1219,\alpha0)}The road of kaki leaves.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:02.03,2:11:04.40,Studio,,0,0,0,,How wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:12.68,2:11:15.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The hardware store is within sight.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:19.52,2:11:24.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All the farms {\alphaFF\t(1553,1553,\alpha0)}It's the height of dried kaki making time so it's more crowded than usual.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:25.99,2:11:29.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The cashier is a friend of her mothers from her preschool.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:29.89,2:11:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:31.36,2:11:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you purchase?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:32.53,2:11:34.33,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,{\pos(469.125,929)}Gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:33.33,2:11:35.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There are so many types of gloves here.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:35.50,2:11:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they tell you what the gloves will be used for?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:37.94,2:11:39.57,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:39.64,2:11:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the size of the gloves?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:42.67,2:11:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's L then is it fine with white ones?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:44.71,2:11:46.61,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,White gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:46.78,2:11:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We have these and these.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:48.51,2:11:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This one?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:50.98,2:11:53.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She picked the correct ones. The box with 100 L gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:56.49,2:11:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it? Did you find the right one?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:59.49,2:12:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Will papa use them?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:01.19,2:12:03.83,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,He's peeling kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:02.33,2:12:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You are all preparing kaki?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:03.83,2:12:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ran out of gloves?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:06.16,2:12:08.50,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,They tore.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:06.96,2:12:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They tore?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:09.47,2:12:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you asked to get something else?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:11.44,2:12:15.77,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,And string to hang kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:13.40,2:12:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And string to hang kaki?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:16.21,2:12:20.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In this area they have a special corner for drying kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:21.28,2:12:24.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The tools change depending on the type of agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:24.75,2:12:28.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So just saying "string" leaves you with many options.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:26.25,2:12:28.59,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:28.22,2:12:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one will do?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:30.45,2:12:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The thin {\alphaFF\t(1193,1193,\alpha0)}or the thick ones. {\alphaFF\t(2461,2461,\alpha0)}Which do you need? Thin?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:35.36,2:12:36.56,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,White.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:36.56,2:12:38.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:38.06,2:12:41.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The one that her family uses is white.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:41.33,2:12:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,For the white strings...
Dialogue: 0,2:12:43.57,2:12:45.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It says: Kaki strings.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:45.57,2:12:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These are specially made for kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:48.77,2:12:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can grip the kaki in between like this.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:51.51,2:12:52.64,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,That's how we do.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:52.64,2:12:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you do it? Then let's go with this one.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:55.15,2:12:58.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's been observant when her father works.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:58.58,2:13:00.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's exactly this type of white string.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:01.09,2:13:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:03.72,2:13:04.99,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,You can do. You can do.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:04.99,2:13:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do? You can do?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:06.92,2:13:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:07.42,2:13:08.46,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,You can do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:08.46,2:13:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You can do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:10.13,2:13:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try you can accomplish it, Riri.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:12.36,2:13:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best. High-five.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:14.70,2:13:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:15.93,2:13:19.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She did it. Yes, she did. She did her best.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:19.60,2:13:22.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And for the 3 O'clock tea time...
Dialogue: 0,2:13:22.14,2:13:25.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And also the bandages to protect her fathers fingers.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:25.64,2:13:29.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She has arrived at the drug store.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:29.51,2:13:31.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Here there's also a specialty corner.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:31.95,2:13:34.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since everyone is preparing kaki these days.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:34.45,2:13:37.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A line-up with great additions for their tea break.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:37.35,2:13:42.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She was asked to get anko dango but {\alphaFF\t(2828,2828,\alpha0)}they are sold out.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:44.16,2:13:47.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But there's anko in these too so they will do.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:47.97,2:13:50.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's hard to make such a decision.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:55.77,2:13:59.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,While considering it she gets the bandages first.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:58.54,2:14:00.54,Studio,,0,0,0,,Remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:59.51,2:14:01.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For a guitarist their fingers are their life.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:01.91,2:14:04.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,So he wraps them in bandage.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:04.11,2:14:07.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She found the bandages right away.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:07.45,2:14:11.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But she's lost in the many types.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:11.32,2:14:14.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Which one should I get?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:14.19,2:14:16.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She can't decide for herself.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:18.40,2:14:22.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She doesn't know any of the store workers {\alphaFF\t(2152,2152,\alpha0)}and without asking any
Dialogue: 0,2:14:22.20,2:14:25.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,she leaves the shop without purchasing anything.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:24.70,2:14:26.70,Studio,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:26.70,2:14:28.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's not confident.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:28.94,2:14:34.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She has become a Ririka who: Can't do it. Can't do her best.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:52.36,2:14:55.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite completing the errand at the hardware store.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:56.33,2:14:58.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She carries a sense of defeat.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:58.84,2:15:03.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And it can be seen on her face as she returns.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:05.11,2:15:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back. {\alphaFF\t(1922,1922,\alpha0)}That was quick.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:08.55,2:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.75,2:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:10.78,2:15:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You bought gloves?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:13.52,2:15:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so great.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:14.99,2:15:17.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even though she's being praised her face says it all.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:17.29,2:15:19.29,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's expected.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:17.96,2:15:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You went and got some? How great.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.43,2:15:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:27.30,2:15:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:29.33,2:15:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the dango?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:30.57,2:15:32.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:32.27,2:15:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you go to Nakaya?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:33.57,2:15:35.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She did go but you see...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:35.37,2:15:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't have dango?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:36.51,2:15:38.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They didn't have dango.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.41,2:15:40.54,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,They only had the soybean ones.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:39.41,2:15:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They only had the soybean ones?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:40.54,2:15:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the green ones would've been fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:41.81,2:15:45.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,See...you could've gotten the green ones.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.82,2:15:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\alpha0\t(2019,0,\alphaFF)}Can you go again?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:47.72,2:15:50.09,Studio,,0,0,0,,She looks so surprised.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:48.99,2:15:50.19,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I want to go with papa.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:50.19,2:15:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:52.42,2:15:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When this is over...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:53.56,2:15:55.23,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Ririka can't go.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:55.23,2:15:57.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She said it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:58.40,2:15:59.83,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:59.26,2:15:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're tired?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:59.83,2:16:02.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But she's not exhausted yet.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:03.50,2:16:05.10,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:05.10,2:16:06.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's a father who
Dialogue: 0,2:16:06.67,2:16:09.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,never scolds his kids or yells at them.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:09.61,2:16:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't have manjyuu what else were you supposed to get?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:14.34,2:16:15.68,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:15.68,2:16:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She has decided not to go.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:17.05,2:16:19.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He knows what she's trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.19,2:16:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.99,2:16:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What a nice sound
Dialogue: 0,2:16:25.06,2:16:26.36,Studio,,0,0,0,,Nice old man.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:28.89,2:16:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We appreciate the gloves but we would also really like to eat some manjyuu.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:33.90,2:16:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Riri, thank you for the gloves.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:37.00,2:16:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But with the tea
Dialogue: 0,2:16:38.74,2:16:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to eat some manjyuu. {\alphaFF\t(1518,1518,\alpha0)}Please, Riri.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:45.11,2:16:46.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And with that...
Dialogue: 0,2:16:46.98,2:16:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ririka, let's go outside.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:48.35,2:16:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, please go.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:49.55,2:16:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a break.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:51.32,2:16:53.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Trying to change her mood.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:53.78,2:16:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We are both pretty tired.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:57.15,2:17:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I play guitar {\alphaFF\t(2394,2394,\alpha0)}my fingers are crucial.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:01.73,2:17:05.80,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,You can just use a pick instead.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:03.96,2:17:05.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:05.80,2:17:08.33,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Then it won't be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:06.86,2:17:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What about this hand?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:08.33,2:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If the fingers on this hand are hurt {\alphaFF\t(2726,2726,\alpha0)}then it will ruin the sound.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:11.97,2:17:13.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She lost the argument.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:14.87,2:17:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they are needed.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:17.31,2:17:18.84,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,What will you do if I trip and fall?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:18.84,2:17:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I will apply a bandage.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:21.78,2:17:24.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ririka won't fall over.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:25.02,2:17:27.88,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I didn't know which type of bandage to get.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:27.88,2:17:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask a store worker loudly?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:30.15,2:17:31.92,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:34.56,2:17:39.30,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I can't use a loud voice.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:35.93,2:17:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then use a quiet voice.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:38.10,2:17:39.83,Studio,,0,0,0,,Trying his best to reason with her.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:39.30,2:17:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's you, Ririka, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:39.90,2:17:41.90,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I feel like eating dango all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:41.90,2:17:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please go and buy some dango.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:44.00,2:17:47.24,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,When mama is done {\alphaFF\t(1590,1590,\alpha0)}I can go with her.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:47.24,2:17:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it will be late and everyone here will go home.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:49.91,2:17:52.14,Studio,,0,0,0,,Seems hard.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:51.54,2:17:56.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Their conversation outside has been going on for 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:56.98,2:18:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\t(5294,0,\alphaFF)}Your extended family members are all doing their best with the Kaki. {\alphaFF\t(3091,3091,\alpha0)\t(5294,0,\alphaFF)}What about you, Ririka?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:04.09,2:18:05.99,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Ririka...
Dialogue: 0,2:18:06.76,2:18:11.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her fathers insistence isn't wavering. He's stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:14.43,2:18:16.23,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:17.23,2:18:19.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's the drone filming them.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:19.60,2:18:21.77,Studio,,0,0,0,,It's going away.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:20.84,2:18:23.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I've been found out.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:23.04,2:18:25.61,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,It's escaping.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:24.17,2:18:26.24,Studio,,0,0,0,,Escaping.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:28.15,2:18:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's concerning.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:29.98,2:18:32.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sorry for intruding.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:32.95,2:18:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ririka, can you read this?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:34.99,2:18:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it. {\alphaFF\t(1951,1951,\alpha0)}Yes, you can. {\alphaFF\t(3520,3520,\alpha0)}You can do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:40.32,2:18:42.53,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,2:18:41.26,2:18:42.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:41.60,2:18:43.38,Studio,,0,0,0,,Remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:42.53,2:18:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:44.26,2:18:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:45.20,2:18:46.53,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,And what if it rains?
Dialogue: 0,2:18:46.53,2:18:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like it will.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:48.13,2:18:50.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's still making excuses.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:51.90,2:18:54.37,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Off I go.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:52.67,2:18:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Off you go.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:54.37,2:18:56.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just like her father insisted.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:56.37,2:18:59.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's on her second errand.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:59.51,2:19:02.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's getting snacks for the 3 O'clock tea.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:02.18,2:19:06.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And bandages to protect her guitar playing father.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:13.62,2:19:15.86,Studio,,0,0,0,,She's playing an instrument.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:19.30,2:19:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to think that she wouldn't go.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:22.30,2:19:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well in revving her engine.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:25.44,2:19:28.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And her fathers new original song: "The road of kaki leaves".
Dialogue: 0,2:19:28.71,2:19:32.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's a song born from the image of Ririka walking on her errand.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:04.74,2:20:07.88,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I can do it. I can do my best.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:07.11,2:20:08.55,Studio,,0,0,0,,Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:07.91,2:20:11.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Can she ask the store worker this time?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:11.35,2:20:12.82,Studio,,0,0,0,,Please do your best.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:12.95,2:20:14.82,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Where do you have dango?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:14.82,2:20:16.32,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,She asked without hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:16.52,2:20:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come to buy dango? Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:19.99,2:20:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry but we've run out today. What to do? Will this do?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:23.43,2:20:25.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That's right. This one will do.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:25.40,2:20:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How many?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:27.16,2:20:28.57,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Six.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:27.80,2:20:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Six?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:28.93,2:20:30.33,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,We are preparing kaki.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:30.33,2:20:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You are preparing Kaki at home today?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:32.74,2:20:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I see, I see. Then you need 6 indeed.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:34.70,2:20:37.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even with a quiet voice she was able to convey it.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:38.01,2:20:41.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since so many of her extended family have come.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:41.81,2:20:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be fine if you get 4 of those and 2 of these?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:44.71,2:20:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you be fine with that?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:46.02,2:20:48.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She goes for it at her own discretion.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:48.95,2:20:51.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The store worker is hurrying towards the checkout.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:51.69,2:20:53.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She better mention the other thing.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:53.49,2:20:55.49,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,And bandages.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:54.56,2:20:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bandages?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:55.49,2:20:57.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She was able to say it.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:58.70,2:21:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a bulk pack. Is that fine?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:00.90,2:21:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you get this then? {\alphaFF\t(1921,1921,\alpha0)}It has 100.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:04.73,2:21:06.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,100 bandages?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:06.10,2:21:09.71,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I don't have the money for 100.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:07.80,2:21:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have the money?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:09.87,2:21:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How many do you need?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:12.18,2:21:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.61,2:21:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't sell just one.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:15.75,2:21:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see... While it has 100 bandages in the pack {\alphaFF\t(4621,4621,\alpha0)}it only costs 149 Yen.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:21.05,2:21:23.22,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's cheap.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:22.39,2:21:24.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's this cheap?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:24.02,2:21:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you get it then?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:25.86,2:21:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's 628 Yen.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:28.33,2:21:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The bandages are for papa, right?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:31.76,2:21:34.60,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,{\t(1690,1690,\fs70)}He plays guitar.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:34.60,2:21:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He plays guitar?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:35.50,2:21:38.60,Studio,,0,0,0,,She's regaining her confidence.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:36.20,2:21:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because he plays guitar {\alphaFF\t(2490,2490,\alpha0)}that he needs to protect his fingers?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:40.20,2:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So he will use them to protect his fingers?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:44.67,2:21:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a bright child.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:45.84,2:21:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take this to papa, your mama and family members.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:49.38,2:21:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:51.72,2:21:54.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even from behind she's beaming with confidence.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:54.62,2:21:56.95,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A huge difference from last time she came.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:03.59,2:22:07.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She was able to. {\alphaFF\t(859,859,\alpha0)}She did it. {\alphaFF\t(1626,1626,\alpha0)}She did her best.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:24.51,2:22:27.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A satisfied face.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:40.46,2:22:45.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She's walking back on the same road as before but there's a big difference.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:46.27,2:22:49.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ririka loves the kaki season.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:49.67,2:22:54.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Because that's the season her father is home instead of away on the usual live tours.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:55.25,2:22:57.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her father is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:57.75,2:23:01.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He's wondering about her face when she opens the door.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:06.02,2:23:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:06.52,2:23:08.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This face.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:08.43,2:23:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back. \NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:12.53,2:23:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazingly quick.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:13.86,2:23:16.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She made it for the 3 O'clock break.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:16.37,2:23:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You got lots of green manjyuu.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:19.10,2:23:20.67,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,They only had four.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:20.67,2:23:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. But you were able to ask the store worker.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:23.27,2:23:25.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But it was with a quiet voice, though.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:25.98,2:23:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How amazing.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:27.88,2:23:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. {\alphaFF\t(1353,1353,\alpha0)}Let's have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:32.62,2:23:34.85,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Enjoy these manjyuu.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:35.32,2:23:38.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Everyone, thank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:37.35,2:23:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the treat.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:39.02,2:23:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. {\alphaFF\t(2492,2492,\alpha0)}You purchased these?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:43.36,2:23:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Delicious.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:45.03,2:23:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How great.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:47.90,2:23:50.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This is also a break to appreciate the work of Ririka.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:50.10,2:23:52.87,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:50.67,2:23:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it delicious?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:52.87,2:23:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:54.60,2:23:58.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Her pâtissier mother has returned from her job.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:58.27,2:23:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you do?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:59.98,2:24:01.18,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,I went shopping.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:01.18,2:24:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Only once?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:02.61,2:24:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You went twice? Why?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:04.11,2:24:07.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There's so much she wants to tell her mother.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:07.18,2:24:09.25,WhitePurpleBorder,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:08.32,2:24:09.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,You see.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:09.39,2:24:12.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Daddy is so stubborn.

